INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (157,15,'2013-01-04 03:07:41','2013-01-04 03:07:41','CommuniLink is a philanthropic social network that connects donors and volunteers with organizations in need in the Northwest Suburbs of Chicago. Explore our site to find out more!\r\n\r\n[button url=\"wp-admin\" color=\"green-lite\" ]Existing User? <strong>Login</strong>[/button] or [button url=\"register\" color=\"orange\" ]New to Our Site? <strong>Register Now</strong>[/button]','What is CommuniLink Chicago?','','inherit','open','open','','18-revision-41','','','2013-01-04 03:07:41','2013-01-04 03:07:41','',18,'http://communilinkchicago.org/archives/157',0,'revision','',0),(127,15,'2013-01-07 13:51:07','2013-01-07 13:51:07','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>WHO WE ARE</strong></p>\nWe are CommuniLink: A philanthropic social network connecting donors and volunteers with organizations in need in the Northwest Suburbs of Chicago.\n\nThrough our social network, organizations are able to post requests for donations or volunteers, and individuals are able to respond to these posts.  Likewise, individuals can post items they have to donate, and also state their availability for volunteer opportunities.\n\nDuring the holidays, we saw how our community came together to provide for those in need largely due to increased awareness. After talking to  community members and leaders, we saw a community-wide willingness to go ‘the extra mile’ during the holiday season. So that sparked a question in our minds:  how can we facilitate this philanthropic spirit year round?\n\nWe realized a way to reduce that extra mile to an extra foot was through utilizing social platforms. We seek to combine social networking and philanthropy to unite the Northwest Suburbs of Chicago.\n\nSee our FAQ section for what types of donation and volunteer opportunities you can use our site for, along with other frequently asked questions.\n\n[button url=\"register\" color=\"orange\" ]New to Our Site? <strong>Register Now</strong>[/button]\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"> <strong>THE FOUNDERS</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://communilinkchicago.org/about-communilink-chicago/dsc_0107\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-150\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-150\" alt=\"DSC_0107\" src=\"http://communilinkchicago.org/wp-content/uploads/DSC_0107-300x239.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"239\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">From left to right - Katie, Natalie, &amp; Tim</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> CommuniLink was founded by Natalie Bounassar, Katie D’Amico, and Tim Zachas in 2012.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Natalie is a future media-mogul with a philanthropic heart. She has been dually called to the arts and philanthropy for her entire life, and saw the chance to apply the project management and communications skills she developed from her extensive work experience to CommuniLink. Natalie will graduate from Columbia College Chicago in May of 2013 with a degree in Media Management. She plans on working with Windy City Live! after graduation.</p>\nKatie was born with a passion for business and bringing about positive change.  After working with various businesses and gaining a diverse skill set, she found the need to apply these skills for the good of her community. Katie graduated in December of 2012 from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign with a degree in Finance and Environmental Economics &amp; Law. She will be working at Deloitte Consulting beginning this winter.\n\nTim has a passion for growing organizations. After developing his skill set through internships in strategy consulting and finance, he saw the opportunity to use his learnings to grow an organization in his local community that has the power to give back. Tim will graduate in June of 2013 from Northwestern University with a degree in Economics and Learning &amp; Organizational Change. He will be working in strategy consulting with The Cambridge Group upon graduation.','About CommuniLink Chicago','','inherit','open','open','','61-autosave','','','2013-01-07 13:51:07','2013-01-07 13:51:07','',61,'http://communilinkchicago.org/archives/127',0,'revision','',0),(128,13,'2012-12-09 19:10:31','2012-12-09 19:10:31','CommuniLink is a web-based resource that strives to improve the lives of those in need by connecting them with donors in their community. We are a non-profit resource founded in 2012 by three individuals striving to make a positive impact at the community level after observing a demand for a previously unmet service.\r\n\r\nTogether, our experience, ambition, and passion will allow us to exceed our goals and grow our organization. We are a web-based resource striving to make a difference in the community through serving as a liaison between parties. our ultimate mission is to connect those with the ability to provide a “good” to another individual who is in need of a “good.” We will be partnering with organizations to allow us to reach our target market of people with a demonstrated need.\r\n\r\n[button url=\"register\" color=\"orange\" ]New to Our Site? <strong>Register Now</strong>[/button]','About Communilink Chicago','','inherit','open','open','','61-revision-4','','','2012-12-09 19:10:31','2012-12-09 19:10:31','',61,'http://communilinkchicago.org/archives/128',0,'revision','',0),(4,1,'2012-11-14 22:01:45','2012-11-14 22:01:45','','Members','','publish','closed','closed','','members','','','2012-11-14 22:01:45','2012-11-14 22:01:45','',0,'http://communilinkchicago.org/communilink/?page_id=4',0,'page','',0),(5,1,'2012-11-14 22:01:45','2012-11-14 22:01:45','','Groups','','publish','closed','closed','','groups','','','2012-11-14 22:01:45','2012-11-14 22:01:45','',0,'http://communilinkchicago.org/communilink/?page_id=5',0,'page','',0),(6,1,'2012-11-14 22:01:45','2012-11-14 22:01:45','','Activity','','publish','closed','closed','','activity','','','2012-11-14 22:01:45','2012-11-14 22:01:45','',0,'http:/