略·ラインであるアウトソールを成形しており、 \"基本的な困難屋外表面や人工芝のために作られている - と一番安い - Mercurialの線のレベル（現在はその第四の生産で、それ故に最新のブーツは、名前の後に \"IV\"を持っています）は最も安い材料で作られており、成長期の子供や人々のためだけに良いですしているMercurialの蒸気、ある彼らはスポーツと滞在したいかわからない人<strong><a href=\"http://www.jeremy-scott.net/categories/1363921906-211.html\">サッカースパイク</a></strong>','スニーカー レディース','','pending','open','open','','','','','2013-04-13 07:11:22','2013-04-13 07:11:22','',0,'http://communilinkchicago.org/?p=237',0,'post','',0),(220,14,'2013-02-24 04:34:55','2013-02-24 04:34:55','<p align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Hiring - Analyst</span></b></p>\r\nThe analyst role at CommuniLink is critical to the overall development of the organization. As an analyst, you will be working with the organizations and individuals using our social platform to understand what niches CommuniLink can best fill. Transition to the analyst role will first begin with external initiatives, with a gradual shift toward critical business strategy projects as CommuniLink grows in the non-profit and social sectors. As an analyst, you will gain exposure to market research, organizational outreach, non-profit strategy, and project management techniques. Upon completion of the analyst program, a successful candidate will be evaluated for a leadership position on the CommuniLink executive team.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Primary responsibilities will include:</strong>\r\n\r\n1)Conducting organizational outreach on behalf of CommuniLink\r\n\r\n2) Developing and refining social media strategy and implementation\r\n\r\n3) Analyzing current membership base to direct expansion efforts\r\n\r\n4) Contributing to a fresh, constantly changing organizational vision\r\n\r\n5) Additional assignments, as needed\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Key benefits include:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>1) Exposure to ground-level operations of a start-up, digital non-profit\r\n\r\n2) Ownership of large, meaningful work streams\r\n\r\n3) Formal and informal mentorship and career advising from founders\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Desired Qualifications:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>1) Current college freshman or sophomore\r\n\r\n2)Minimum 3.3 GPA\r\n\r\n3) Self-starter, capable of contributing 10-15 hours per week to CommuniLink\r\n\r\n4) Prior business-related experience preferred<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">About CommuniLink</span></b></p>\r\nCommuniLink is a start-up not-for-profit organization operating out of the Northern Suburbs of Chicago, seeking to connect donors and volunteers with organizations in need through social networking. Founded by three individuals in 2012, CommuniLink is still in its developmental stages, allowing all team members to make a significant impact to the future of the organization. More information can be found at <a href=\"http://www.communilinkchicago.org\">http://www.communilinkchicago.org</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How to Apply </span></b></p>\r\nIf you are interested in applying for the position, please e-mail an updated version of your resume and cover letter to <a href=\"mailto:communilink2012@gmail.com\">communilink2012@gmail.com</a>. All questions regarding the position can be directed to Tim Zachas, Director of Strategy, at <a href=\"mailto:tim.zachas@gmail.com\">tim.zachas@gmail.com</a>.\r\n\r\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></b>','CommuniLink is hiring!','','publish','open','open','','communilink-is-hiring','','','2013-02-24 04:34:55','2013-02-24 04:34:55','',0,'http://communilinkchicago.org/?p=220',0,'post','',0),(222,14,'2013-02-24 04:33:09','2013-02-24 04:33:09','<p align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Analyst</span></b></p>\nThe analyst role at CommuniLink is critical to the overall development of the organization. As an analyst, you will be working with the